description:
&lt;p&gt;The Acute Medicine directorate are looking for motivated, enthusiastic and innovative band 5 nurse to join our AEC nursing team. AEC is part of the Acute Medical team and we have a workforce model focused on providing safe and effective patient care, and leadership and development of the nursing team. You will be offered excellent training and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In this post you will be responsible for the initial assessment of patients, and providing an effective care pathway within AEC. We are committed to developing a culture in line with our values that improves quality and enhances the patient experience, and you will play a vital part in developing new ways of working to achieve this goal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Candidates will be a first level registered nurse. You must be flexible to the demands of the service and be able to work as part of a multidisciplinary team. Excellent communication skills are essential for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hours: Full time over 7 day period including bank holidays, 12 hour shifts, long day (07.00-19.30), middle shift (08.30-21.00) and twilight (10.30-23.00)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruth Bradbury Senior Sister ruth.bradbury@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01782 671700&lt;/p&gt;
